The United Nations publishes the full Reprt of the Secretary-General's Panel of Experts on Accountability In Sri Lanka which finds "credible allegations" which, if proven, indicate that war crimes and crimes against humanity were committed both by the Government of Sri Lanka and the LTTE in the final stages of the Sri Lankan Civil War. (UN News Centre) (BBC) (Al Jazeera) (The Australian)Yuri Budanov, a Russian colonel convicted of strangling an 18-year-old Chechen girl during the Chechen War, is shot dead in Moscow. (AFP via Google News) (RIA Novosti)